<anchor xml:id="_zroc__error_8h_1a2fd7a0b4bad0021bf4e749b184c96968"/><section>
    <title>zroc_err_get()</title>
<indexterm><primary>zroc_err_get</primary><secondary>zroc_error.h</secondary></indexterm>
<indexterm><primary>zroc_error.h</primary><secondary>zroc_err_get</secondary></indexterm>
<para><computeroutput><link linkend="_structZrocErr">ZrocErr</link> * zroc_err_get (void )</computeroutput></para><para>

<para>Get the thread-local error object. </para>
</para>

<para>If the thread does not have an error object yet, one will be allocated and initialized with code <computeroutput>ZROC_OK</computeroutput> and an empty message.</para>

<para><formalpara><title>Returns</title>

<para>Pointer to the thread-local <link linkend="_structZrocErr">ZrocErr</link> object. </para>
</formalpara>
</para>
</section>
<anchor xml:id="_zroc__error_8h_1ac3b5134d4b68d73b4648c2c8d024bbe8"/><section>
    <title>zroc_err_set()</title>
<indexterm><primary>zroc_err_set</primary><secondary>zroc_error.h</secondary></indexterm>
<indexterm><primary>zroc_error.h</primary><secondary>zroc_err_set</secondary></indexterm>
<para><computeroutput>void zroc_err_set (<link linkend="_zroc__error_8h_1a6340f7a28709f8192fa324ff4f07bc7f">ZrocErrCode</link> code, const char * msg)</computeroutput></para><para>

<para>Set the thread-local error. </para>
</para>

<para>Updates the thread-local error code and message. If <computeroutput>msg</computeroutput> is <computeroutput>NULL</computeroutput>, the default message for the given <computeroutput>code</computeroutput> from <computeroutput>ZROC_ERRORS</computeroutput> will be used.</para>

